<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbfb73a1b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s13261"><num value="13261">§ 13261.</num><heading> Prohibited acts</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">It shall be unlawful for any person to violate any provision of section 13251, 13253(b), 13257, or 13263a of this title, or any regulation issued under such sections.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbfb73a1c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/102/486/tV/s511">Pub. L. 102–486, title V, § 511</ref>, <date date="1992-10-24">Oct. 24, 1992</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/106/2899">106 Stat. 2899</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/109/58/tVII/s703/b">Pub. L. 109–58, title VII, § 703(b)</ref>, <date date="2005-08-08">Aug. 8, 2005</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/119/816">119 Stat. 816</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idbfb73a1d-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">
